Didn't say you did suggest that. I agreed with you. Just reinforced that the focus would always be how failure shows up and what it does to people and businesses. Also suggested investors could talk about the non-investables". Thanks!"
Anyway, congrats on the event.

Didn't meant to suggest moving away from Failure, just that different types of businesses involve different types of risk and subsequently different types of failures. Eg. What the impact of failure for a mom that decided to launch her small venture at 37?

Good tip. The focus will always be Failure and yes, that can be applied to all types of businesses (after the session, I spoke to Alexandre a little about that, actually). Maybe investors talking about this would be helful also.
